  "prompt": "How did you react when your parents didn't buy you a new mobile?",
  "response": "When my parents didn't buy me a new mobile, I was initially disappointed because I had been looking forward to it. However, I tried to understand their perspective\u2014maybe it wasn't the right time financially, or they felt it wasn't necessary. I reminded myself of the importance of gratitude for what I already have and used the opportunity to improve my patience and responsible spending habits. Over time, I realized that material possessions aren't everything, and my parents' decisions are often made with my best interests in mind.",
